Identify High and Low Tides¶

In [8]: 
##-- Find min & max from dataset
decluster = 5

# for local maxima
localmax = array( argrelextrema(data.values, np.greater_equal) )
localmax = localmax[0, (localmax[0,1:] - localmax[0,:-1]) > decluster ]

# for local minima
localmin = array( argrelextrema(data.values, np.less_equal) )
localmin = localmin[0,  (localmin[0,1:] - localmin[0,:-1]) > decluster ]

# Plot tides with high and low marked in red
fh = pyplot.figure(figsize=(20, 6), dpi=120)
data.plot(color='blue')
data.ix[localmax].plot(color='red', marker='.')
data.ix[localmin].plot(color='red', marker='.')

Divide HHW/HW and LLW/LW¶

In [9]: 
##-- Find higher high water and lower low water

# Collect high and low values.  Clear ends, since they're skewed by the boundary.
high = data.ix[localmax][1:-1]
low = data.ix[localmin][1:-1]

# Calculate Higher High and High tides
mask = zeros(shape(high))
for i in xrange(len(high) - 1):
   if high[i] >= high[i+1]: mask[i] = 1
if high[-1] > high[-2]: mask[-1] = 1

# Check for skipped higher high's
for i in xrange(2,len(mask)-2):
    if sum(mask[i-1:i+3])<0.5: mask[i]=1
    
hw = high[mask==0]
hhw = high[mask==1]

# Calculate Lower Low and Low tides
mask = zeros(shape(low))
for i in xrange(len(low) - 1):
   if (low[i] <= low[i+1]): mask[i] = 1
if low[-1] < low[-2]: mask[-1] = 1
    
# Check for skipped lower lows
for i in arange(1,len(mask)-1,1):
    if sum(mask[i-1:i+2])<0.5: mask[i]=1
    if sum(mask[i-1:i+2])>2.5: mask[i]=0
    
###print(mask)
lw = low[mask==0]
llw = low[mask==1]

# Plot time series
fh = pyplot.figure(figsize=(20, 6), dpi=120)
data.plot(color='blue')
hw.plot(color='red', marker='.')#, ls='None')
hhw.plot(color='green', marker='.')#, ls='None')
lw.plot(color='red', marker='.')#, ls='None')
llw.plot(color='green', marker='.')#, ls='None')

(1) Select closest and next two more extreme cases¶

In [67]: 
##-- Find high tides near mhhw, mhw, mlw, and mllw

# Select three MHHW tides
diffVal = high.values-mhhw
targets = high.ix[diffVal>=0]
mhhw_tg = targets.ix[targets.values.argsort()[:3]]

# Select three MHW tides
diffVal = high.values-mhw
targets = high.ix[diffVal>=0]
mhw_tg = targets.ix[targets.values.argsort()[:3]]

# Select three MLW tides
diffVal = low.values-mlw
targets = low.ix[diffVal<=0]
mlw_tg = targets.ix[targets.values.argsort()[-3:]]

# Select three MLLW tides
diffVal = low.values-mllw
targets = low.ix[diffVal<=0]
mllw_tg = targets.ix[targets.values.argsort()[-3:]]

##-----------------------------------------------------
##-- Tides Selected for use
##-----------------------------------------------------

t1 = mllw_tg.sort_index().index[0]
t4 = mhw_tg.sort_index().index[2]

##-----------------------------------------------------

# Plot tide record and closest Spring/Neap HHW & LLW
fh = figure(figsize=(20, 6), dpi=120)
data.plot(color='blue')

plot(axis()[:2], [mhhw,mhhw], 'g--', lw=2)
plot(axis()[:2], [mhw,mhw], 'r--', lw=2)
plot(axis()[:2], [mlw,mlw], 'r--', lw=2)
plot(axis()[:2], [mllw,mllw], 'g--', lw=2)

mhhw_tg.plot(color='g',marker='o',ms=8,ls='None')
mhw_tg.plot(color='r',marker='o',ms=8,ls='None')
mlw_tg.plot(color='r',marker='o',ms=8,ls='None')
mllw_tg.plot(color='g',marker='o',ms=8,ls='None')

title('Tide Selection at The Battery')

##-- Find high tides near mhhw, mhw, mlw, and mllw

# Select three MHHW tides
diffVal = high.values-mhhw
targets = high.ix[diffVal>=0]
mid = int(len(targets)/2)
mhhw_tg = targets.ix[targets.values.argsort()[mid:mid+3]]

# Select three MHW tides
diffVal = high.values-mhw
targets = high.ix[diffVal>=0]
mid = int(len(targets)/2)
mhw_tg = targets.ix[targets.values.argsort()[mid:mid+3]]

# Select three MLW tides
diffVal = low.values-mlw
targets = low.ix[diffVal<=0]
mid = int(len(targets)/2)
mlw_tg = targets.ix[targets.values.argsort()[mid-3:mid]]

# Select three MLLW tides
diffVal = low.values-mllw
targets = low.ix[diffVal<=0]
mid = int(len(targets)/2)
mllw_tg = targets.ix[targets.values.argsort()[mid-3:mid]]
